    "body": "### Problem\n\nhi folks!\r\ncurrently the only way is using fn.undotree(), while it's relatively heavy as it contains the whole undo tree, especially i trend to have a big &undolevels, say 1000.\r\n\r\nassume i have such mapping `nnoremap gq my_format` to trigger a format operation, and input `gq u <c-r> gq` occasionally.\r\ni want to avoid my_format() being ran at the second `gq`, as `u <c-r>` implies there is no changes.\r\nand `b:changedtick` wont help here, since `u` and `<c-r>` always increase it.\r\n\r\nso i need a way to get the undo block info after `gq`, and compare it with the one when i raise gq again.\r\nalso from what i know `undo!` can clear part of the undo history, so i should use seq and time togger.\r\n\r\nthe problem originally came from [here](https://github.com/nvimdev/guard.nvim/issues/27)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\na cheap way to get the current undo block info",
